org.dotplot.fmatrix
Class TypeTable

java.lang.Object
  org.dotplot.fmatrix.TypeTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class TypeTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class is used as a datastorage for token types in the sense of the fMatrix. It uses a Hashtable to implement datastructures(store TokenType objects) and provides methods to access and modify data.

The implemented Hashtable will not take duplicate entries.

See Also:
TokenType, Serialized Form

TypeTable

public TypeTable(TokenTable tokenTable)
Constructor receiving a reference on two TokenTable objects, which will be filled by an instance of this class. This constructor is used in a case where a token source is to be plotted against another token source(if 2nd source is null, the 1st source will)

Parameters:
tokenTable - the tokenTable to be used.
